File: Eskom eNCA JOHANNESBURG - While power utility Eskom has suspended load-shedding for the long weekend, it announced load reduction in four provinces will be taking place on Thursday afternoon. The load reduction will take place between 5 pm and 9 pm on Thursday. READ: Eskom suspends load-shedding for long weekend In Limpopo, residents in Mopani Districts will be affected. In the Free State, Fezile Dabi District will be experiencing load reduction. KwaZulu-Natal and Mpumalanga will also be experiencing power cuts. Eskom Load Reduction Notice
